ps and venture funds and founders that other banks wouldn=E2=80=99t make, a=
t attractive rates, thus attracting loyal customers; it also required some =
of those borrowers to keep their cash at SVB, making those deposits contrac=
tually sticky. But those relationships did not really save SVB, and part of=
 the reason might be that SVB=E2=80=99s customers, enthusiastic as they wer=
e, were tech-savvy business customers who were on the internet all day, and=
