olor: #ccc;"> Politico reports today</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That tension has created one hell of an openin=
g for crypto-friendly Republicans like House Financial Services Chair Patri=
ck McHenry of North Carolina and Agriculture Chair G.T. Thompson of Pennsyl=
vania, who=E2=80=99ve been trying to build bipartisan support for a crypto =
bill that would grant new powers to the Commodity Futures Trading Commissio=
n =E2=80=94 the industry=E2=80=99s preferred regulator =E2=80=94 and defang=
 the SEC.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The decision =E2=80=9Crecognizes what Republic=
ans have said all along,=E2=80=9D the two chairs said in a joint statement =
on Friday evening. =E2=80=9CThere is a limit to the SEC=E2=80=99s reach.=E2=
=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Democratic leaders like Rep. Maxine Waters of =
California, the ranking Democrat on Financial Services, as well as Sen. Eli=
zabeth Warren of Massachusetts frequently echo SEC Chair Gary Gensler=E2=80=
=99s assertion that most crypto activity already falls under the agency=E2=
=80=99s purview. Few Democrats have strayed from that view =E2=80=94 partic=
ularly since the stunning collapse of Sam Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s FTX late =
last year.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Ripple ruling scrambles that argument. Wit=
h McHenry having tentatively scheduled a markup on the crypto market struct=
ure bill for Wednesday (and Thompson saying he wants his committee to mark =
up the legislation before August recess), the Ripple ruling could create a =
lane for GOP leaders to peel off more Democrats to back the measure.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Before Thursday=E2=80=99s ruling, =E2=80=9Cit =
wasn=E2=80=99t resonating,=E2=80=9D one senior Republican committee staffer=
 involved in the drafting said late Friday. =E2=80=9CMaybe when we start ag=
ain next week =E2=80=94 when they=E2=80=99re back =E2=80=94 it will resonat=
e.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Ripple ruling, on its face, seems to make =
it very hard to protect retail investors from crypto fraud or to mandate an=
y sort of disclosures about new crypto projects.=C2=A0Reversing that ruling=
