 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">a great Wall Street prank</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The night JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co. agreed to b=
uy the bank for $2 a share, a $2 bill was taped to the revolving door of Be=
ar Stearns=E2=80=99s headquarters =E2=80=94 a prank that created one of the=
 defining images of the financial crisis. But the people behind it remained=
 a secret. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In reality, the prank was committed by three t=
hen-20-something year-old friends and former Columbia University roommates =
who had no direct ties to the firm. While one of them =E2=80=94 Bartek Ring=
welski =E2=80=94 had been an analyst at UBS Group AG until 2007, and anothe=
r =E2=80=94 Alex Davidov =E2=80=94 went on to spend four years at Bridgewat=
er Associates, their careers have been more focused on tech than Wall Stree=
t.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe were joking around, =E2=80=98Would=
n=E2=80=99t it be funny to tape a $2 bill to the headquarters?=E2=80=99=E2=
=80=9D Ringwelski, now the founder of a venture fund, said by phone. =E2=80=
=9COur goal at the time was to get this into <em>Dealbreaker</em>.=E2=80=9D=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Davidov happened to have a stack of eighteen $=
2 bills that he=E2=80=99d been gifted for his bar mitzvah; he kept them in =
a box that bounced around with him all the way to his Brooklyn apartment.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Armed with one of the unusual bills and packin=
g tape, the three men descended on Bear=E2=80=99s Madison Avenue headquarte=
rs late in the evening on the March night that JPMorgan announced its offer=
. Davidov and Andrew McDaniel took the subway from Brooklyn, while Ringwels=
ki walked over from his midtown apartment.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThere were surprisingly not many peop=
le around the building,=E2=80=9D McDaniel said. =E2=80=9CSo we just taped i=
t to the door and took a few pictures ourselves. And then we emailed it to =
<em>Dealbreaker</em>.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">McDaniel emailed the photos from an anonymous =
account he set up for the prank: Sexyjefferson@yahoo.com.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is from Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Katia Porzeca=
nski, who solved this mystery on Friday. Disclosure, I used to write for=C2=
=A0<em>Dealbreaker</em>, though not in 2008, and it warms my heart that, in=
 the depths of the financial crisis, their first thought was =E2=80=9Clet=
=E2=80=99s get into=C2=A0<em>Dealbreaker</em>.=E2=80=9D The traditional way=
 to do that was with a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
