 sharing part of a translation of Homer=E2=80=99s Odyssey in which Odysseus=
, lost at sea for days and afraid he will die, finally reaches land. In the=
 portion shared by Kumar, Odysseus swims and finally finds a peaceful river=
, then pulls himself ashore.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI now come to your stream, here at yo=
ur knees, after enduring so many struggles. Have pity on me, Lord. I declar=
e myself your suppliant,=E2=80=9D the passage reads in part. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Kumar said that he had not seen the trial resu=
